                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d486">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51W89 Italy/290: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-06-08T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 8, 1936—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 8—6:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>199. Department’s 56, June 5, 5 p.m. I called by appointment on the Minister of
                    Finance this morning and communicated to him the substance of the Department’s
                    instruction referred to above. He said he would confer with the Chief of the
                    Government on the matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
